    {
      "id": "pbks-take-top-spot",
      "title": "PBKS hold top spot — Prabhsimran 83* & Iyer 66 stitch 139 to shrug off de Kock's 112*",
      "body": "Punjab Kings remain the table-toppers after their 7-wicket win at Wankhede on April 16. Chasing 196, openers Prabhsimran Singh (83* off 60) and captain Shreyas Iyer (66 off 41) put on 139 in just 67 balls to nullify a stunning Quinton de Kock 112* off 60 balls for MI. PBKS are now 4-0 on the pitch with one washout, 9 points and a +1.067 NRR at the summit.",
      "tag": "On Fire"
    },
    {
      "id": "gill-grabs-orange-cap",
      "title": "Gill steals Kohli's Orange Cap — 251 in 4, tops a tight top-5",
      "body": "Shubman Gill has leapfrogged Virat Kohli to the top of the IPL 2026 run charts with 251 runs in just 4 innings, averaging 62.75 at a strike rate of 154.94. Kohli (228) slips to 2nd, with Heinrich Klaasen (224), RCB skipper Rajat Patidar (222) and Ishan Kishan (213) all within 40 runs of the leader. Patidar's tournament-high 21 sixes and Sooryavanshi's 263 SR keep the race spicy.",
      "tag": "Sensation"
    },
    {
      "id": "prasidh-leads-purple",
      "title": "Prasidh goes solo at the top — 11 wickets and the best average in the Purple Cap race",
      "body": "Gujarat Titans' Prasidh Krishna is now the outright Purple Cap leader with 11 wickets in 5 matches at an average of 16.73, after striking in today's win over KKR. CSK's Anshul Kamboj (10) is a wicket behind, while Prince Yadav and Ravi Bishnoi (9 each) keep LSG in the chase. Jofra Archer's 8.47 economy is the best among top wicket-takers.",
      "tag": "Breakout"
    },
